hiddenMarkovModels
==================

python code to simulate ensemble dynamical models (Rapela et al., 2015).

To simulate an ensemble dynamical model, of integrate and fire neurons,
driven by excitatory and inhibiotory sinusoidal currents, run the script
doTestIFEnsembleDensityIntegratorRWFWI.py (with python 2.7) from the directory
test/simulations/omurtagSig:

cd test/simulations/omurtagSim; python2.7 doTestIFEnsembleDensityIntegratorRWFWI.py

This script will save two figures, rhosSinusoidalRWFWIPopulationKMu0.0300.eps
and spikeRatesSinusoidalRWFWIPopulationKMu0.0300.eps, containing the
integrated ensemble probability density function and the spike rate of the
ensemble dynamical model.

this function to estimate hidden Markov models with multivariate Gaussian
(test/doTestMGaussian.R) and with Poisson observations. Poisson observations
are modeled without autohistory (test/doTestPoisson.R)
and with autohistory (test/doTestPoissonGLM.R).

doc/hmmPoissonGLM.pdf documents the evaluation of the estimation of Hidden
Markov Models with Poisson observations with autohistory in simulated data and
in multiunit activity count recordings from a subject with epilepsy.

Rapela  J., Kostuk M, Rowat, P.F., Mullen, T., Chang E.F., Bouchard K. (2015)
Modeling  neural activity at the ensemble level.
http://arxiv.org/abs/1505.00041
